track_notes: This is a 2 mile hike with the first 0.9 miles on the Arizona Trail.  Park at the Gordon Hirabayashi Campground.  Note this could be a good choice for a double as the parking is right at the base of Peak 5471, another 6 pointer. Once you leave the AZT its a scramble along the ridgeline and there are a couple of places with false peaks.  Use a GPS or app to make sure you reach the correct summit.
track_title: Gibbon Mountain UP - from Gordon Hirabayashi Campground

track_notes: The first half of the hike is on the Arizona Trail. The second half is a bushwhack from Shreve Saddle to the summit. On a scale of 0-10 for hike difficulty, this hike rates a 7.4 but you get only 6 points for it. See my track for the descent which shows some variation from the ascent.
track_title: Gibbon Mountain Ascent from Gordon Hirabayashi CG

track_notes: Some slight variations from the ascent that might be slightly better because the perspective on the descent is often better than on the ascent.

This route takes advantage of a small trail that comes off the AZ trail.  It is a faint trail and disappears occasionally, and eventually you will need to do some bushwhacking, and ultimately it rejoins the other route along the ridge near the top.  I thought it was a slightly more scenic route, but its not what I would call easy.
